{"timestamp": "2025-12-12 05:18:22.978629", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: **Anomaly detected**\\n\\n- The ping from `switch_access_1_1_1` to `router_core_1` (and vice‑versa) fails with *“Network is unreachable”*.\\n- The `switch_access_1_1_1` has no IP address configured on any of its interfaces (br0, eth0‑eth4 all show only MAC addresses and no `inet` entries).\\n\\n**Localization**\\n\\n- The fault is on the access switch `switch_access_1_1_1`.  \\n- All other devices (router, other switches, hosts) appear to have valid IP addresses and routing entries.\\n\\n**Root cause**\\n\\n- The access switch has not been assigned an IP address on the interface that connects to the core router.  \\n- Without an IP, the switch cannot participate in the IP layer, so packets cannot be routed to or from the core router, resulting in the “Network is unreachable” error.\\n\\n**Next steps (if mitigation is required)**\\n\\n1. Assign a proper IP address to the interface on `switch_access_1_1_1` that connects to the core router (e.g., `10.1.1.x/24` with the core router’s neighbor `10.1.1.y`).\\n2. Verify that the switch’s default gateway (if needed) points to the core router.\\n3. Re‑run the ping test to confirm connectivity., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='c28a417d-9039-4c86-8b3e-09e3066cfec8'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "not_implemented", "id": ["langchain_ollama", "chat_models", "ChatOllama"], "repr": "ChatOllama(model='gpt-oss:20b', validate_model_on_init=True, temperature=0.0, base_url='http://10.68.186.140:11434')", "name": "ChatOllama"}}
